The paper discusses the development of a domain-specific language for implementing high-performance finite-difference partial differential equation solvers for geophysical exploration, specifically in seismology. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
